### 5.1 Die Newton-Gravitation im Code

Die Formel $F = G \frac{M_1 M_2}{r^2}$ wird in der Java-Simulation wie folgt operationalisiert:


```java

// Java-Implementierung der Materie-Doktrin "Gravitation"

public class GravitySimulation {

    public static final double G = 6.67430e-11; // Gravitationskonstante


    public Vector2d calculateForce(Unit mass1, Unit mass2) {

        double dx = mass2.posX - mass1.posX;

        double dy = mass2.posY - mass1.posY;

        double distanceSq = dx*dx + dy*dy;

        double distance = Math.sqrt(distanceSq);

        

        // F = G * (m1 * m2) / r^2

        double forceMagnitude = (G * mass1.mass * mass2.mass) / distanceSq;

        

        return new Vector2d(

            (dx / distance) * forceMagnitude,

            (dy / distance) * forceMagnitude

        );

    }

}

```

